## Why This Is Asked
Evaluates practical data protection across SAP on AWS with Snowflake analytics, balancing real-time access and compliance.

## Key Concepts
- SAP S/4HANA data ingestion and masking
- Field-level masking rules for PII
- Snowflake masking policies and data sharing
- AWS KMS key management and IAM governance
- Auditing, rollback, and failover strategies

## Code Example
```javascript
// Example masking function
function maskPII(record) {
  const r = {...record};
  if (r.email) r.email = r.email.replace(/(.{2}).+(@.*)/, '$1***$2');
  if (r.phone) r.phone = r.phone.replace(/(\d{3})\d{4}(\d{3})/, '$1***$2');
  if (r.ssn) r.ssn = '***-**-' + r.ssn.slice(-4);
  return r;
}
```

## Follow-up Questions
- How would you validate masking without leaking data in logs?
- How would you rotate keys and propagate policy changes across Snowflake without downtime?

